lead_paragraph: Crop and livestock losses from storms and floods in California this month now exceed $500 million, the California Department of Food and Agriculture said on Friday. The department's figure of $507.6 million was up from an estimate of $400 million earlier this week, with the latest number reflecting losses from areas just reporting. The total could rise further, a department spokeswoman said, as a few counties have not yet reported their losses.

headline.main: California Crop Loss Put at $500 Million
